What you need to know:

With seven titles under their belt, the Pharaohs are Africa’s most successful Nations Cup countryThere isn’t that big difference between Thursday night’s clash with that of 1987 except for the Covid-dictated empty terraces and the masksIf the government was serious about developing football in the country, it should induce a Fifa ban by disbanding FKF and then use the time to carry out far-reaching youth development programmes